What is a pipe in Angular?
A pipe is used to transform data in the template before displaying it to the user.
Pipe does not change the original data, only the view.

Example (Without Pipe)
{{ user.role }} o/p=> ADMIN
With Pipe
{{ user.role | roleDisplay }}  o/p==> Administrator

Date Pipe

  date:Date= new Date(2001,7,4)  (7 = august 0 based index)
shortDate   mediumDate  longDate  fullDate  shortTime   mediumTime   longTime

If the date comes from an API (string â†’ Date)
this.date = new Date(apiResponse.date);

<h4>{{date|date:'shortDate'}}</h4>
   <h4>{{date|date:'fullDate'}}</h4>

<td>{{ event.eventDate | date:'dd-MMM-yyyy hh:mm a' }}</td>

UpperCase / LowerCase Pipe
{{ user.name | uppercase }}
{{ user.name | lowercase }}
{{ user.name | titlecase }}
Currency Pipe
{{ event.price | currency:'INR' }}

Slice Pipe
{{ user.name | slice:0:5 }}

decimal pipe
{{ 1234.567 | number }}

number:'minInteger.minFraction-maxFraction'

1. What is the JSON Pipe?

The JSON pipe is used to display an object or array as readable JSON text in the template.

users = [
  { id: 1, name: 'John' },
  { id: 2, name: 'Sara' }
];
Output:

[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "John"
  },
  {
    "id": 2,
    "name": "Sara"
  }
]

